
[1]inpolitic

   INPOL'ITIC, a. Not wise; devising and pursuing measures adapted to
   injure the public interest; as an impolitic prince or minister.

   1. Unwise; adapted to injure the public interest; as an impolitic law,
   measure or scheme.

   2. Not wise in private concerns; pursuing measures ill suited to
   promote private welfare; not prudent.

   3. Not suited to promote private interest.
